    • Constructor Detail

      • OpenAjaxHubFactory

        public OpenAjaxHubFactory(boolean handleMessageIfInactive,
                  java.lang.String... subscribedChannels)
        Simplified version of the factory constructor, that utilizes default OAH handlers, i.e. initialization, connection, activation, event callbacks are processed by default implementation of this factory
        Parameters:
        handleMessageIfInactive - true if widget should receive events if inactive
        subscribedChannels - List of channels to which the widget should subscribe. If widget is calling D2 action services, it must subscribe to D2_EVENT_CUSTOM event

      • OpenAjaxHubFactory

        public OpenAjaxHubFactory(boolean handleMessageIfInactive,
                  com.google.gwt.user.client.rpc.AsyncCallback<HubConnectionMessage> connectCompletedCallback,
                  com.google.gwt.user.client.rpc.AsyncCallback<java.lang.Boolean> activeWidgetCallback,
                  com.google.gwt.user.client.rpc.AsyncCallback<OpenAjaxMessage> initWidgetCallback,
                  com.google.gwt.user.client.rpc.AsyncCallback<HubEventMessage> oahCallback,
                  java.lang.String... subscribedChannels)
        Default constructor of the factory, allowing to provide custom callback to all OAH events (initialization, connection, activation, event).
        Parameters:
        handleMessageIfInactive - true if widget should receive events if inactive
        connectCompletedCallback - Callback raised when OAH connection is established (might be an notification of a connection error as well)
        activeWidgetCallback - Callback raised on widget activation
        initWidgetCallback - Callback raised on widget initialization
        oahCallback - Callback raised on event to which the widget has subscribed
        subscribedChannels - List of channels to which the widget should subscribe. If widget is calling D2 action services, it must subscribe to D2_EVENT_CUSTOM event
